This software builds on the following third-party open-source projects
(each under its own license):
  - dinosaur-dycore (Google Research) — Apache License 2.0
    The active multi-level atmosphere is this differentiable JAX spectral
    dynamical core (the engine behind NeuralGCM). See Kochkov et al. (2024)
    and https://github.com/google-research/dinosaur.
  - JAX, Optax (Google / Google DeepMind) — Apache License 2.0
  - NumPy, SciPy, xarray, netCDF4, Matplotlib — BSD-3-Clause / permissive
  - Pooch (data fetching), cdsapi (Copernicus Climate Data Store client)
    — BSD-3-Clause / Apache License 2.0

This software ingests the following third-party DATA PRODUCTS. Users must
cite these datasets in any publication that uses Chronos-ESM results
(full references in docs/manual/references.bib and docs/ATTRIBUTION.md):
  - World Ocean Atlas 2018 (WOA18), temperature & salinity — NOAA NCEI
    (Locarnini et al. 2018; Zweng et al. 2018). Ocean initial conditions,
    SST/SSS restoring, and validation.
  - ERA5 reanalysis — Copernicus Climate Change Service / ECMWF
    (Hersbach et al. 2020). Atmospheric validation benchmark.
  - ETOPO1 Global Relief Model — NOAA NGDC
    (Amante & Eakins 2009). Orography, ocean depth, and land/sea masks.
  - RAPID-MOCHA 26.5°N AMOC array (Smeed et al. 2018) — observational
    AMOC benchmark (~17 Sv).
  - Atmospheric CO2 record — NOAA Global Monitoring Laboratory / IPCC AR6.
  - Total solar irradiance (1361 W/m^2) — Kopp & Lean (2011).
